Even the transformers movies get more love from their fans. text: SPOILERS IF YOU HAVEN'T SEEN THE MOVIE   I hate to say it but, Pitch Perfect somehow turned into Glee. It became less about the singing and music and more about the drama and useless plot. Seriously, what was the point of that whole thing with Fat Amy's dad and the boat? There was no actual acapella riff-off, hardly any Stacey, no Treblemakers or Tonehangers? Lily was possessed by Satan the whole time?? wtf?? It would have been better if Lily was just...like that for no reason. Fat Amy, who couldn't even manage 'vertical running,' is suddenly a master of martial arts? Also the whole Chloe and Becca obvious sexual tension thing, let's just throw that in the garbage. Yeah Chloe grabbed Becca's boobs but hey let's just pair Chloe up with this random army dude and have the creepy, British producer guy constantly breathing down Becca's neck. Also I miss Jesse, Bengi and Bumper.     Wow I didn't mean to write that much, I just thought this movie was lame. I'm gonna go watch the first movie and just not acknowledge the third movie as canon.
